<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-18T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-18T16:00:00-05:00" n="814" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d814">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R./1096: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-18T16:00:00-05:00">May 18,
                                    1940—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 5 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>70. My telegram No. 69. At the suggestion of Uruguayan Foreign Minister
                            Dr. Garay has just furnished the press the following additional
                            communiqué: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“In connection with the joint declaration of the American
                                    Republics the Panamanian Foreign Office states that the
                                    Government of Colombia, in adhering to the said document,
                                    expressed the desire that the names of Denmark and Norway be
                                    added to those of the three countries whose neutrality has been
                                    violated by the German forces.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>